@subsection Connection Establishment Phase

A pair of queues is associated with an @value{SHORT} association between two @value{SHORT} addresses
when the @value{SHORT} receives an @prim{MTP_CONN_REQ} primitive at one of the @value{SHORT}
addresses resulting in a connect object being entered into the queue.  The queues will remain
associated with the @value{SHORT} association until an @prim{MTP_DISCON_REQ} primitive (resulting in
a disconnect object) is either entered or removed from a queue.  Similarly, in the queue from the
remote @value{SHORT}-User, objects can be entered into the queue only after the connect object
associated with an @prim{MTP_CONN_REQ} has been entered into the queue.

The @value{SHORT} association procedure will fail if the @value{SHORT} is unable to route to the
remote @value{SHORT}-User.

