@node Protocol Address Acknowledgement
@subsection Protocol Address Acknowledgement

@subsubheading MTP_ADDR_ACK
@prindex MTP_ADDR_ACK

This primitive acknowledges the corresponding request primitive and is used by the @value{SHORT} to
return information concerning the local and remote protocol addresses for the stream.

The format of the message is one @msg{M_PCPROTO} message block and its structure is as follows:

@smallexample
typedef struct MTP_addr_ack @{
        mtp_ulong mtp_primitive;        /* always MTP_ADDR_ACK */
        mtp_ulong mtp_loc_length;       /* length of local @value{SHORT} address */
        mtp_ulong mtp_loc_offset;       /* offset of local @value{SHORT} address */
        mtp_ulong mtp_rem_length;       /* length of remote @value{SHORT} address */
        mtp_ulong mtp_rem_offset;       /* offset of remote @value{SHORT} address */
@} MTP_addr_ack_t;
@end smallexample
@tpindex struct MTP_addr_ack
@tpindex MTP_addr_ack_t

@subsubheading Parameters

@vtable @var
@item mtp_primitive
Indicates the primitive type.  This field is always coded MTP_ADDR_ACK.
@item mtp_loc_length
Indicates the length of the local @value{SHORT} address (@value{SHORT}-SAPI).  If the stream is not
bound to a local @value{SHORT}-SAPI, this field will be coded zero (0).
@item mtp_loc_offset
Indicates the offset of the local @value{SHORT} address (@value{SHORT}-SAPI) from the start of the
@msg{M_PCPROTO} message block.  If the stream is not bound to a local @value{SHORT}-SAPI, this field
will be coded zero (0).
@item mtp_rem_length
Indicates the length of the remote @value{SHORT} address (@value{SHORT}-SAPI).  If the stream is not
connected to a remote @value{SHORT}-SAPI, this field will be coded zero (0).
@item mtp_rem_offset
Indicates the offset of the remote @value{SHORT} address (@value{SHORT}-SAPI) from the start of the
@msg{M_PCPROTO} message block.  If the stream is not connected to a remote @value{SHORT}-SAPI, this
field will be coded zero (0).
@end vtable

@subsubheading Valid State

This primitive is valid in state MTP_WACK_AREQ.

@subsubheading New State

The new state is the state previous to the MTP_ADDR_REQ.

@subsubheading Rules

@itemize ---
@item
If the requesting stream is not bound to an @value{SHORT} address (@value{SHORT}-SAPI), the
@value{SHORT} will code the @var{mtp_loc_length} and @var{mtp_loc_offset} fields to zero.
Otherwise, the @value{SHORT} will return the same @value{SHORT} address that was returned in the
MTP_BIND_ACK.
@item
If the requesting stream is not associated with a remote peer (i.e, not bound in a signalling
relation), the @value{SHORT} will code the @var{mtp_rem_length} and @var{mtp_rem_offset} fields to
zero.  Otherwise, the @value{SHORT} will indicate the remote @value{SHORT} address
(@value{SHORT}-SAPI) of the associated remote @value{SHORT}-User.
@end itemize

