This section describes the format of the COMS primitives and the rules associated with these
primitives.  The default values of the options parameters associated with an @value{SHORT}
association may be selected via the @prim{MTP_OPTMGMT_REQ} primitive.

@node Signalling Relation Establishment Phase
@subsection Signalling Relation Establishment Phase

The following @value{SHORT} service primitives pertain to the establishment of an association
between local and remote @value{SHORT}-SAPs, provided the @value{SHORT} users exist, and are known
to the @value{SHORT}.

@subsubsection @value{LONG} Connection Request
@subsubheading MTP_CONN_REQ
@prindex MTP_CONN_REQ

This primitive requests that the @value{SHORT} form an association to the specified destination.

@subsubheading Format
@tpindex struct MTP_conn_req
@tpindex MTP_conn_req_t

The format of the message is one @msg{M_PROTO} message block.  The structure of the @msg{M_PROTO}
message block is as follows:

@smallexample
typedef struct MTP_conn_req @{
        mtp_ulong mtp_primitive;        /* always MTP_CONN_REQ */
        mtp_ulong mtp_addr_length;      /* length of @value{SHORT} address to connect */
        mtp_ulong mtp_addr_offset;      /* offset of @value{SHORT} address to connect */
        mtp_ulong mtp_conn_flags;       /* connect flags */
@} MTP_conn_req_t;
@end smallexample

@subsubheading Parameters

@vtable @var
@item mtp_primitive
Specifies the primitive type.  This field is always coded MTP_CONN_REQ.
@item mtp_addr_length
Specifies the length of the @value{SHORT} address (@value{SHORT}-SAPI) of the peer to which a
signalling relation is to be established.  If no @value{SHORT} address is provided by the
@value{SHORT}-User, this field must be coded zero (0).  The coding of the @value{SHORT} address
(@value{SHORT}-SAPI) is protocol and provider-specific.
@item mtp_addr_offset
Specifies the offset of the @value{SHORT} address (@value{SHORT}-SAPI) from the beginning of the
@msg{M_PROTO} message block.
@item mtp_conn_flags
Indicates a bit field of connection options.  (See @emph{Flags} below.)
@end vtable

@subsubheading Flags

@subsubheading Rules

The following rules apply to the establishment of associations between the specified addresses:

@itemize ---
@item
If the @var{mtp_addr_length} field in the MTP_CONN_REQ primitive is zero, then the @value{SHORT} is
to select a remote @value{SHORT} address (@value{SHORT}-SAPI) with which to associate.  If the
@value{SHORT} cannot select a address for the association, the @value{SHORT} responds with an
MTP_ERROR_ACK primitive with error MNOADDR.
@item
If the @var{mtp_addr_length} field in the MTP_CONN_REQ primitive is non-zero, the @value{SHORT} is
to associate with the specified remote @value{SHORT} address (@value{SHORT}-SAPI).  if the
@value{SHORT} cannot associate with the specified remote @value{SHORT} address (@value{SHORT}-SAPI),
the primitive will fail and the @value{SHORT} will return an MTP_ERROR_ACK primitive with the
appropriate error value (e.g, MBADADDR).
